Return to lay
here is currently only 1 known case of  recurrence. aron and colleaguesβ€™ 2001 series21 demonstrated that 71% (15 of 21) achieved complete physical recovery and 29% (6 of 21) had mild to moderate residual neurologic disability or cardiac impairment (as manifested by reduced left ventricular ejection fraction) at follow-up between 1 and 20 years.
 survivors should undergo a thorough cardiac evaluation, including a 12-lead electrocardiogram, ambulatory olter monitoring, exercise stress testing, and echocardiogram.20 lectrophysiologic testing and implantable cardioverter defibrillator are not generally recommended.20 eturn-to-play decisions should be made on a case-to-case basis.
here is concern regarding individual susceptibility to chest wall-induced , based on data from the swine model1; thus, return to play in contact sports must be balanced against a possibly increased risk of recurrence.Return to Play
There is currently only 1 known case of CC recurrence. Maron and colleaguesβ€™ 2001 series21 demonstrated that 71% (15 of 21) achieved complete physical recovery and 29% (6 of 21) had mild to moderate residual neurologic disability or cardiac impairment (as manifested by reduced left ventricular ejection fraction) at follow-up between 1 and 20 years.
CC survivors should undergo a thorough cardiac evaluation, including a 12-lead electrocardiogram, ambulatory Holter monitoring, exercise stress testing, and echocardiogram.20 Electrophysiologic testing and implantable cardioverter defibrillator are not generally recommended.20 Return-to-play decisions should be made on a case-to-case basis.
There is concern regarding individual susceptibility to chest wall-induced CC, based on data from the swine model1; thus, return to play in contact sports must be balanced against a possibly increased risk of recurrence.
